    "body": "Summary\r\n\r\n### Expected Result\r\n\r\ntcltk capability should be true\r\n\r\n### Actual Result\r\n\r\ntcltk capability is false\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ spack install r +X\r\n$ module load r-3.4...\r\n$ R\r\n$ > capabilities(\"tcltk\")\r\n$ FALSE\r\n...\r\n```\r\n1. tcl & tk listed as dependence, so by default R should be compiled with tcltk option\r\n2. Default installtion didn't work, so added '--with-tcltk\" to config_args, still got the same result\r\n\r\n\r\n### Information on your system\r\n\r\nCentos 7, gcc 7.2",
